loan_history:
[< Slovak/Czech] < Latin olīva < Greek ἐλαίϝα < some Mediterranean source (cf. Buck 1949: 380);
< Slovak/Czech < Latin oliva < Greek elaia (Holub & Kopečný 1952: 254);
< Slovak/Czech < Latin oliva < Greek elaia < probably pre-European (Holub & Lyer 1978: 318)

cf. also
1. Slovak/Czech < Greek naftha < Assyrian (Holub & Kopečný 1952: 238);
2. Slovak/Czech < Medieval Latin naphta < Greek naftha < “Iranian origin” (Holub & Lyer 1978: 304)
